  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>onion</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong>over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and cook for 4 min or until it's softened and&nbsp;translucent</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, bring a large&nbsp;pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>&nbsp;with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, add the<strong>&nbsp;lasagne verdi sheets</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>one at a time,&nbsp;with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> between each one (this stops them sticking together)</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 12 min or until they have softened and cooked</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> dried&nbsp;</strong><strong>oregano</strong> and 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong> to&nbsp;the pan&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>butter</strong> has melted, stir in 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 2 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Stir 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span>&nbsp;<strong>milk</strong> gradually into the pan&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Whisk constantly for 3-5min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains, then add the <strong>shredded&nbsp;kale</strong>, cover&nbsp;and cook for 3 min or until the kale has started to wilt&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once wilted, crumble the <strong>feta</strong> into the&nbsp;<strong><strong>kale&nbsp;</strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>Remove from the heat, add a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and set aside - this is your<strong>&nbsp;kale &amp; feta sauce&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> and set aside&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>baby plum tomatoes</strong> in half&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>basil leaves</strong> from the stalks and chop the stalks finely, leaving the <strong>leaves</strong> whole &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped&nbsp;tomatoes</strong> and the <strong>basil leaves</strong> (keep the stalks for later) to a bowl with a splash of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a&nbsp;pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Give everything a gentle mix up - this is your <strong>tomato &amp; basil salad</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/970.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Check the <strong>lasagne sheets</strong> are cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return them to the pot with a little&nbsp;<strong>starchy</strong> <strong>pasta water</strong> (this prevents them from sticking together)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
